00:28:57.501 --> 00:28:59.335
Grab my lily.

252
00:29:01.964 --> 00:29:04.466
That skirt you're chasing
must have moved ahead.

253
00:29:05.134 --> 00:29:09.053
- We gotta hightail it to the hog, pronto.
- To the hog?

254
00:29:09.889 --> 00:29:13.224
The engine. The engine,
you tenderfoot.

255
00:29:13.392 --> 00:29:16.603
We gotta make the engine
before we hit Flat Top Tunnel.

256
00:29:16.770 --> 00:29:18.438
How come?

257
00:29:18.606 --> 00:29:21.232
So many questions.

258
00:29:21.650 --> 00:29:25.987
There is but one inch of clearance
between the roof of this rattler...

259
00:29:26.155 --> 00:29:29.032
and the roof of Flat Top Tunnel.

260
00:29:29.200 --> 00:29:31.075
Savvy?

261
00:29:34.205 --> 00:29:37.248
It's just the run up
to the hump, kid.

262
00:29:38.083 --> 00:29:39.751
This will be interesting.

263
00:30:02.942 --> 00:30:04.651
Get back on, kid. Hurry!

264
00:30:04.818 --> 00:30:07.111
Grab my muck stick.

265
00:30:42.815 --> 00:30:45.316
There's only one
trick to this, kid.

266
00:30:46.485 --> 00:30:47.986
When I say "jump"...

267
00:30:50.406 --> 00:30:54.325
you jump!

268
00:31:17.141 --> 00:31:20.310
You. I thought you got
thrown off, and...

269
00:31:20.686 --> 00:31:23.521
- You're driving the train?
- They put me in charge.

270
00:31:23.689 --> 00:31:27.108
- The engineer had to check the light.
- Here's the light. Careful.

271
00:31:27.276 --> 00:31:28.943
All right, now.

272
00:31:31.071 --> 00:31:32.572
I got it.

273
00:31:35.284 --> 00:31:38.786
- How do you know how?
- It's easy. Come here, I'll show you.

274
00:31:38.954 --> 00:31:41.414
This big lever here,
that's the throttle.

275
00:31:41.582 --> 00:31:43.708
This little one here,
that's the brake.

276
00:31:43.876 --> 00:31:46.753
And those are the
pressure gauges.

277
00:31:46.920 --> 00:31:49.505
And that rope is the whistle.

278
00:31:50.174 --> 00:31:51.883
The whistle.

279
00:31:52.676 --> 00:31:54.594
You wanna try it?

280
00:31:57.431 --> 00:32:00.433
I've wanted to do
that my whole life.

281
00:32:03.979 --> 00:32:07.148
Hold still! Hold still!
Don't move!

282
00:32:08.317 --> 00:32:09.359
Look!

283
00:32:21.580 --> 00:32:25.041
Stop the train! Stop the train!

284
00:32:26.085 --> 00:32:27.919
Stop the train!

285
00:32:30.881 --> 00:32:32.590
What?

286
00:32:32.758 --> 00:32:35.426
They want us to stop the train.

287
00:32:35.594 --> 00:32:38.054
- Which one is the brake?
- He told me this was.

288
00:32:38.222 --> 00:32:39.931
- Who?
- The engineer.

289
00:32:40.140 --> 00:32:44.727
- The engineer? This one looks like a brake.
- No, he said this was the brake.

290
00:32:44.895 --> 00:32:48.731
Are you sure?

291
00:32:55.823 --> 00:32:58.533
Pull the brake!

292
00:32:58.742 --> 00:33:00.618
Stop the train!

293
00:33:17.970 --> 00:33:19.929
Caribou?

294
00:33:22.474 --> 00:33:26.352
There can be no Christmas without
the Polar Express arriving on time.

295
00:33:26.520 --> 00:33:29.814
Am I the only one who
understands that?

296
00:33:29.982 --> 00:33:32.775
You. I should have known.

297
00:33:32.943 --> 00:33:36.821
Are you bound and determined that this
train never reaches the North Pole?

298
00:33:36.989 --> 00:33:38.573
But look.

299
00:33:39.825 --> 00:33:41.492
Caribou crossing?!

300
00:33:42.327 --> 00:33:46.080
I make that herd to be at least
100,000, maybe even a million.

301
00:33:46.248 --> 00:33:49.333
It's gonna be hours before
they clear this track.

302
00:33:49.501 --> 00:33:53.546
- A tough nut to crack.
- We are in some serious jelly.

303
00:33:53.714 --> 00:33:56.174
- And a jam.
- Tight spot.

304
00:33:56.341 --> 00:33:57.675
- Up a creek.
- Up a tree.

305
00:33:57.843 --> 00:34:01.053
- Lost in the grass.
- I'll tell you what's grass: Our a...

306
00:34:43.472 --> 00:34:47.892
Problem solved. All ahead, slow.

307
00:35:33.856 --> 00:35:35.773
We're going pretty fast.

308
00:35:35.941 --> 00:35:38.818
Tell the engineer to slow down.

309
00:35:44.157 --> 00:35:45.783
Slow it down.

310
00:35:47.661 --> 00:35:50.413
Watch the speed!

311
00:35:55.460 --> 00:35:58.504
Jumping jeepers, the
cotter pin sheared off.

312
00:35:58.672 --> 00:35:59.964
- What?
- The pin.

313
00:36:00.132 --> 00:36:02.300
- Where?
- There.

314
00:36:02.467 --> 00:36:04.010
- Oh, no.
- Oh, no.

315
00:36:05.053 --> 00:36:07.972
- They can't hear me.
- They can't?

316
00:36:11.476 --> 00:36:13.895
I don't like the look of this.
Under the safety bar.

317
00:36:16.273 --> 00:36:17.953
Is everything all right?
What should we do?

318
00:36:18.108 --> 00:36:22.570
Considering we've lost
communication with the engineer...

319
00:36:22.738 --> 00:36:25.907
we are standing totally exposed
on the front of the locomotive...

320
00:36:26.074 --> 00:36:29.243
the train appears to be
accelerating uncontrollably...

321
00:36:29.411 --> 00:36:33.247
and we are rapidly
approaching Glacier Gulch...

322
00:36:33.415 --> 00:36:36.918
which happens to be the steepest
downhill grade in the world...

323
00:36:37.085 --> 00:36:40.379
I suggest we all hold on...

324
00:36:40.923 --> 00:36:43.174
tightly.

325
00:37:03.362 --> 00:37:05.196
- The pin.
- The pin.

326
00:37:24.883 --> 00:37:28.594
Jiminy Christmas, the ice
has frozen over the tracks.

327
00:37:50.993 --> 00:37:53.160
Hold on. Hold on. No, no.

328
00:37:54.079 --> 00:37:56.205
Come on. Watch your step.

329
00:37:56.373 --> 00:37:59.583
Come on, sweetie. Up you go.
Up you go.

330
00:38:02.045 --> 00:38:04.505
Put your feet on here. On here.

331
00:38:07.050 --> 00:38:08.342
Little adventure, huh?

332
00:38:08.510 --> 00:38:10.928
Young man, quick
thinking on your part.

333
00:38:32.034 --> 00:38:34.785
Step to your left, please.
To your left.

334
00:38:38.623 --> 00:38:42.126
Well, that is more like it.

335
00:38:44.504 --> 00:38:47.214
What in the name of Mike?

336
00:38:50.343 --> 00:38:51.802
Look.

337
00:38:54.431 --> 00:38:57.183
Get us the blazes out of here!

338
00:39:05.442 --> 00:39:07.026
Turn this sled around.

339
00:39:25.504 --> 00:39:26.921
Look there.

340
00:39:29.633 --> 00:39:30.966
Tracks.

341
00:39:31.134 --> 00:39:32.551
Dead ahead.

342
00:39:38.391 --> 00:39:39.517
Right.

343
00:39:45.357 --> 00:39:46.357
Left.

344
00:39:51.863 --> 00:39:52.863
Right.

345
00:39:56.743 --> 00:39:57.993
Hang a Louie.

346
00:40:01.123 --> 00:40:02.498
Toss a Ritchie.

347
00:40:05.877 --> 00:40:07.545
Port astern.

348
00:40:09.714 --> 00:40:11.549
To the starboard.

349
00:40:12.843 --> 00:40:15.427
- My slipper.
- You're gonna lose your ticket.

350
00:40:15.595 --> 00:40:17.471
It's not my ticket, it's yours.

351
00:40:17.639 --> 00:40:19.473
- It's my ticket?
- Yes.

352
00:40:19.641 --> 00:40:21.767
Right. Keep up with me. Left.

353
00:40:22.102 --> 00:40:24.520
Right. Left.

354
00:40:28.567 --> 00:40:29.900
Right.

355
00:40:30.235 --> 00:40:31.527
Left.

356
00:40:31.695 --> 00:40:33.070
Right.

357
00:40:33.238 --> 00:40:35.197
Left. Right.

358
00:40:38.910 --> 00:40:40.202
- Oh, no!
- Oh, no!

359
00:40:42.414 --> 00:40:44.248
Brace yourselves!

360
00:40:55.302 --> 00:40:57.219
Well, that's more like it.

361
00:40:59.598 --> 00:41:01.140
Thank you.

362
00:41:01.308 --> 00:41:04.602
Thank you. I can't believe
you found my ticket.

363
00:41:05.145 --> 00:41:07.771
Did someone say they
found a ticket?

364
00:41:09.774 --> 00:41:13.194
Well, in that case...
Tickets, please.

365
00:41:22.078 --> 00:41:23.621
Thank you.

366
00:41:25.332 --> 00:41:29.251
- "L-E"?
- Just like that know-it-all kid.

367
00:41:44.184 --> 00:41:46.769
Watch your step.
Tricky walking up here.

368
00:41:46.937 --> 00:41:49.313
It's mighty slick.
Mighty slick, I tell you.

369
00:41:50.482 --> 00:41:53.025
There you go.
What did I tell you?

370
00:41:53.193 --> 00:41:58.322
Years ago, on my first Christmas Eve run,
I was up on the roof making my rounds...

371
00:41:58.490 --> 00:42:00.407
when I slipped on
the ice myself.

372
00:42:00.575 --> 00:42:03.994
I reached out for a hand iron, but
it broke off. I slid and fell.

373
00:42:04.162 --> 00:42:08.165
And yet, I did not
fall off this train.

374
00:42:08.750 --> 00:42:11.001
Someone saved you?

375
00:42:11.169 --> 00:42:13.170
Or something.

376
00:42:16.049 --> 00:42:17.341
An angel.

377
00:42:18.260 --> 00:42:19.927
Maybe.

378
00:42:20.095 --> 00:42:22.179
Wait. Wait.

379
00:42:23.014 --> 00:42:26.183
What did he look like?
Did you see him?

380
00:42:27.310 --> 00:42:31.188
No, sir. But sometimes
seeing is believing.

381
00:42:31.564 --> 00:42:36.694
And sometimes the most real things in
the world are the things we can't see.

382
00:42:42.534 --> 00:42:44.868
The forsaken and the abandoned.

383
00:42:46.037 --> 00:42:50.040
Mind your step, now. These poor
toys have suffered enough...

384
00:42:50.208 --> 00:42:54.545
being left to rust and decay in the back
alleys and vacant lots of the world.

385
00:42:55.046 --> 00:42:59.216
- What are they doing here?
- It's a new concept the boss came up with.

386
00:42:59.384 --> 00:43:02.761
Instead of being thrown away,
they're collected. Refurbished.

387
00:43:03.471 --> 00:43:08.559
He calls it "rebicycling."
Something like that.

388
00:43:10.812 --> 00:43:13.230
Makes me wanna cry...

389
00:43:13.398 --> 00:43:16.567
seeing toys that were
treated this way.

390
00:43:17.360 --> 00:43:21.572
These hopelessly entangled string
puppets and marionettes...

391
00:43:21.740 --> 00:43:26.035
pose a particular problem. We found the
nimble fingers of our work force...

392
00:43:26.202 --> 00:43:30.539
here at the North Pole are best for
working out those knots and tangles.

393
00:43:30.707 --> 00:43:33.250
Thank you. Double-locked here.

394
00:43:44.637 --> 00:43:48.098
You are just like me, my friend.

395
00:43:48.266 --> 00:43:50.642
A scrooge!

396
00:43:50.810 --> 00:43:52.978
Ebenezer Scrooge.

397
00:43:53.146 --> 00:43:56.482
North Pole, Santa
Claus, this train...

398
00:43:56.649 --> 00:44:00.569
it's all a bunch of humbug.
A bout of indigestion.

399
00:44:00.737 --> 00:44:03.322
Oh, yeah. I know what you are.

400
00:44:03.490 --> 00:44:06.116
You're a doubter.

401
00:44:06.284 --> 00:44:08.827
A doubter. You don't believe!

402
00:44:08.995 --> 00:44:12.164
You're a doubter!
You don't believe!

403
00:44:29.265 --> 00:44:32.184
You missed it. We rode down
some really sharp hills.

404
00:44:32.352 --> 00:44:36.730
We were on what looked like a frozen lake.
But I know it was just an optical illusion.

405
00:44:36.898 --> 00:44:39.817
He said the train was on ice.
I said it's impossible...

406
00:44:39.984 --> 00:44:42.694
You can't put a train track...
Where you going now?

407
00:44:57.210 --> 00:45:00.170
I'm wishing on a star.

408
00:45:00.338 --> 00:45:03.507
And trying to believe.

409
00:45:03.675 --> 00:45:06.844
That even though it's far.

410
00:45:07.303 --> 00:45:09.847
He'll find me Christmas Eve.

411
00:45:10.473 --> 00:45:13.600
I guess that Santa's busy.

412
00:45:13.768 --> 00:45:16.770
'Cause he's never come around.

413
00:45:17.272 --> 00:45:23.026
I think of him When
Christmas comes to town.

414
00:45:23.820 --> 00:45:26.989
The best time of the year.

415
00:45:27.157 --> 00:45:30.367
When everyone comes home.

416
00:45:30.535 --> 00:45:33.704
With all this Christmas cheer.

417
00:45:33.872 --> 00:45:37.416
It's hard to be alone.

418
00:45:37.584 --> 00:45:43.630
Putting up the Christmas tree
With friends who come around.

419
00:45:43.798 --> 00:45:50.179
It's so much fun When
Christmas comes to town.

420
00:45:50.972 --> 00:45:57.060
Presents for the children
Wrapped in red and green.

421
00:45:57.604 --> 00:46:03.400
All the things I've heard
about But never really seen.

422
00:46:04.235 --> 00:46:06.737
No one will be sleeping.

423
00:46:06.905 --> 00:46:09.990
On the night of Christmas Eve.

424
00:46:10.158 --> 00:46:17.247
Hoping Santa's on his way.

425
00:46:17.415 --> 00:46:20.501
When Santa's sleighbells ring

426
00:46:20.668 --> 00:46:23.545
I listen all around.

427
00:46:23.713 --> 00:46:26.924
The herald angels sing

428
00:46:27.091 --> 00:46:30.093
I never hear a sound.

429
00:46:30.637 --> 00:46:34.097
And all the dreams of children.

430
00:46:34.265 --> 00:46:37.059
Once lost will all be found.

431
00:46:37.227 --> 00:46:45.227
That's all I want When
Christmas comes to town.

432
00:47:05.713 --> 00:47:07.172
Look.

433
00:47:09.842 --> 00:47:11.843
The northern lights.

434
00:47:14.681 --> 00:47:16.723
Hey. You three.

435
00:47:17.934 --> 00:47:19.726
We just crossed it.

436
00:47:19.894 --> 00:47:25.315
Latitude 66°33'.
The Arctic Circle.

437
00:47:25.483 --> 00:47:28.819
And do you see?
Those lights in the distance.

438
00:47:29.737 --> 00:47:34.199
They look like the lights of a strange
ocean liner sailing on a frozen sea.

439
00:47:35.493 --> 00:47:37.494
There...

440
00:47:38.162 --> 00:47:40.205
is the North Pole.

441
00:47:45.211 --> 00:47:48.046
It's a magic carpet on a
rail It never takes a rest.

442
00:47:48.214 --> 00:47:51.383
Flying through The
mountains and the snow.

443
00:47:51.551 --> 00:47:54.511
You can ride for free and join
the fun If you just say yes.

444
00:47:54.679 --> 00:47:58.015
'Cause that's the way things
happen On the Polar Express.

445
00:47:58.182 --> 00:48:01.310
Whoo, whoo, the whistle blows
That's the sound of her singing.

446
00:48:01.477 --> 00:48:04.688
Ding, ding, the bell will
ring Golly, look at her go.

447
00:48:04.856 --> 00:48:07.858
You wonder if you'll get
there soon Anybody's guess.

448
00:48:08.026 --> 00:48:11.236
'Cause that's the way things
happen On the Polar Express.

449
00:48:11.404 --> 00:48:14.531
When we get there
We'll scream, "Yay!"

450
00:48:14.699 --> 00:48:17.034
We'll arrive with A
bang, bang, bang.

451
00:48:17.201 --> 00:48:20.203
Boom, boom, boom
Laughing all the way.

452
00:48:25.209 --> 00:48:28.128
We made it. With five
minutes to spare.

453
00:48:28.296 --> 00:48:30.172
We made it.

454
00:48:55.615 --> 00:48:57.908
There should be elves.
Where are the elves?

455
00:48:58.076 --> 00:48:59.743
Yeah, where are the elves?

456
00:48:59.911 --> 00:49:02.245
They are gathering in
the center of the city.

457
00:49:02.413 --> 00:49:06.208
That is where Santa will give
the first gift of Christmas.

458
00:49:07.085 --> 00:49:09.544
Who gets the first
gift of Christmas?

459
00:49:09.712 --> 00:49:13.590
He will choose one of you.

460
00:49:16.803 --> 00:49:19.596
- Look.
- Elves!

461
00:49:50.461 --> 00:49:52.796
All right. All right,
ladies and gentlemen.

462
00:49:52.964 --> 00:49:55.674
Two columns, if you please.

463
00:49:55.842 --> 00:49:58.635
Shorter in the front,
taller in the rear.

464
00:49:59.137 --> 00:50:02.764
Even-numbered birthdays on the
right, odd-numbered on the left.

465
00:50:02.932 --> 00:50:05.851
No pushing. No pushing.
But let's not dilly-dally.

466
00:50:06.018 --> 00:50:07.936
It's five minutes to midnight.

467
00:50:08.104 --> 00:50:11.690
Hey, what gives? It was five minutes
till midnight four minutes ago.

468
00:50:12.150 --> 00:50:14.651
Exactly. Columns of two.

469
00:50:14.819 --> 00:50:16.945
- One, two.
- Excuse me.

470
00:50:17.113 --> 00:50:19.573
- Question.
- What about him?

471
00:50:22.326 --> 00:50:25.036
No one is required to see Santa.

472
00:50:26.164 --> 00:50:29.374
Ladies and gentlemen, you do
not have to hold hands...

473
00:50:29.542 --> 00:50:33.003
- Come on.
- But please remain in your columns...

474
00:50:33.171 --> 00:50:35.547
while we are in transit.

475
00:50:45.183 --> 00:50:48.685
- Look, you have to come with us.
- She's right.

476
00:50:50.605 --> 00:50:55.066
Christmas just doesn't work
out for me. Never has.

477
00:50:55.234 --> 00:50:57.861
But Christmas is such a
wonderful, beautiful time.

478
00:50:58.029 --> 00:51:01.656
It's a time for giving and being
thankful, for friends and family.

479
00:51:01.824 --> 00:51:06.620
People hang decorations and lights. Santa
leaves presents under our Christmas trees.

480
00:51:08.539 --> 00:51:10.290
Christmas just...

481
00:51:10.875 --> 00:51:12.751
doesn't work out for me.

482
00:51:14.545 --> 00:51:18.256
Look, I don't know if Christmas is
gonna work out for you or not...

483
00:51:18.424 --> 00:51:21.551
but this is Christmas Eve.
Don't stay here by yourself.

484
00:51:23.221 --> 00:51:24.763
Yes, come with us.

485
00:51:25.306 --> 00:51:27.098
We'll go together.

486
00:51:39.195 --> 00:51:40.821
Oh, no.

487
00:51:48.871 --> 00:51:50.747
We're gonna be okay.

488
00:51:53.084 --> 00:51:55.210
Maybe not!

489
00:51:57.088 --> 00:52:01.174
The emergency brake.

490
00:52:04.887 --> 00:52:08.682
There's no brake.
I can't find the brake!

491
00:52:15.189 --> 00:52:17.774
Take a break, kid.

492
00:52:17.942 --> 00:52:21.611
How about a nice,
good hot cup of Joe?

493
00:52:50.224 --> 00:52:51.308
We're gonna crash!

494
00:52:58.316 --> 00:53:00.233
We're spinning.

495
00:53:26.010 --> 00:53:27.969
You hear that?

496
00:53:28.554 --> 00:53:29.846
The bell.

497
00:53:31.223 --> 00:53:33.600
- What bell?
- The sleighbell.

498
00:53:33.768 --> 00:53:36.186
- Sleighbell?
- Don't you hear it?

499
00:53:37.521 --> 00:53:40.065
It's coming from that tunnel.

500
00:53:45.613 --> 00:53:47.739
That's the way we should go.

501
00:53:56.207 --> 00:53:57.749
Come on.

502
00:54:29.949 --> 00:54:31.533
What?

503
00:54:32.034 --> 00:54:34.703
- What?
- Come on.

504
00:54:46.716 --> 00:54:47.716
