Santa's been here!

769
01:28:42.833 --> 01:28:46.753
Mom, Dad, look! He brought
us all kinds of stuff!

770
01:28:46.920 --> 01:28:49.464
Look, a train!

771
01:29:05.856 --> 01:29:11.360
This is the beautiful-est, most
wonderful-est Christmas ever.

772
01:29:11.528 --> 01:29:13.821
Wait. Look.

773
01:29:15.115 --> 01:29:16.991
Here's one more.

774
01:29:18.535 --> 01:29:20.411
Has your name on it.

775
01:29:49.399 --> 01:29:51.901
Found this on the
seat of my sleigh.

776
01:29:52.069 --> 01:29:54.737
Better fix that hole
in your pocket.

777
01:29:54.905 --> 01:29:56.155
Mr. C.

778
01:30:06.208 --> 01:30:09.377
Oh, what a beautiful bell.
Who's it from?

779
01:30:09.545 --> 01:30:11.587
- Santa.
- Santa?

780
01:30:11.755 --> 01:30:13.381
Really?

781
01:30:14.424 --> 01:30:16.843
- Oh, that's too bad.
- What's this?

782
01:30:17.886 --> 01:30:19.387
Broken.

783
01:30:20.514 --> 01:30:22.682
Sorry about that, sport.

784
01:30:27.229 --> 01:30:30.356
Come on, kids.
We don't wanna be late.

785
01:30:38.407 --> 01:30:41.909
At one time, most of my
friends could hear the bell.

786
01:30:42.077 --> 01:30:46.122
But as years passed, it fell
silent for all of them.

787
01:30:46.290 --> 01:30:51.586
Even Sarah found, one Christmas, that she
could no longer hear its sweet sound.

788
01:30:51.753 --> 01:30:53.421
Though I've grown old...

789
01:30:53.589 --> 01:30:55.965
the bell still rings for me.

790
01:30:56.133 --> 01:31:00.219
As it does for all
who truly believe.

